## v1.1.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** Second-round (R1) planning re-learning for Odysseus issue #71
("Agamemnon/Nestor in-memory stores need persistent backing"). The R0 plan
(v1.0.0) proposed SQLite-WAL behind the existing C++ `Store` API but FLAGGED
several unverified external-dependency assumptions for the reviewer. This R1 pass
turned those flagged risks into VERIFIED-by-inspection decisions by reading the
actual repo config (`conanfile.py`, `cmake/StaticAnalyzers.cmake`,
`cmake/CompilerWarnings.cmake`, `cmake/StandardSettings.cmake`,
`cmake/SourcesAndHeaders.cmake`) and cross-repo skills. This AMENDS the same skill
rather than duplicating it.

**Verification:** unverified — nothing was built or run this pass either. The R1
decisions are grounded in inspected config files and in-repo precedent, but no
`conan install`, `just deps`, `just lint`, or `ctest` was executed.

### What changed

- **MINOR bump (1.0.0 -> 1.1.0):** new findings + new Failed Attempts rows +
  extended workflow. The core R0 heuristic (test-harness-driven backing-store
  choice; prefer in-process/embedded over networked store when the suite runs
  without that network dep) is UNCHANGED and remains primary.
- **Reversed the dependency-mechanism decision.** R0 said "use a hand-written
  FetchContent URL for SQLite, do NOT introduce Conan." R1 inspected
  `conanfile.py` and found the repo ALREADY pulls every dep via Conan
  (`self.requires("cpp-httplib/...")`, `self.requires("nlohmann_json/...")`,
  resolved by `find_package(... REQUIRED)`). New decision: add
  `self.requires("sqlite3/3.46.0")` + `find_package(SQLite3 REQUIRED)` and link
  the prebuilt `SQLite::SQLite3` imported target. This eliminates the guessed
  amalgamation URL AND removes the self-compiled `sqlite3_amalg` static-lib
  target. (The R0 "FetchContent is the repo idiom" claim was itself the kind of
  unverified premise this skill warns against.)
- Added the general lesson: when a plan introduces a new third-party lib, prefer
  the project's existing package-manager path (Conan/vcpkg/etc.) over a
  hand-written FetchContent/URL fetch — it removes an unverifiable assumption and
  inherits the project's pinning/caching.
- Added the CI-gate-strictness verification step: read
  `cmake/StaticAnalyzers.cmake` (clang-tidy ON + cppcheck `--enable=all` ON;
  `CMAKE_CXX_CLANG_TIDY` applied to every project source),
  `cmake/CompilerWarnings.cmake` (`-Werror`), `cmake/StandardSettings.cmake`
  (`WARNINGS_AS_ERRORS=ON`). Raw SQLite C-API (owning `sqlite3_stmt*`,
  `reinterpret_cast` on `sqlite3_column_text`) WILL trip clang-tidy/cppcheck under
  -Werror; mirror the existing `nats_client.cpp` NOLINT precedent (lines 3, 177,
  184) and add a `just lint` + `ctest --preset ci` verification step.
- Added the package-manager-vs-self-compiled liability point: a self-compiled dep
  target is a warnings-as-errors liability; Conan's prebuilt `SQLite::SQLite3`
  imported target sidesteps `-Werror`/`WARNINGS_AS_ERRORS` for sqlite3.c entirely
  (you never compile it yourself) — only your `store.cpp` (which CALLS the API)
  stays subject to the gates.
- Added the build-constraint-premise check: confirmed `SourcesAndHeaders.cmake`'s
  exclusion comment is about `main.cpp`'s `main()` symbol, not store sources —
  `store.cpp` has no `main()`, so linking it into the Agamemnon library is safe.
- Added the response-shape-citation point: the restart-survival test reads
  `create_team(...)["team"]["id"]` / `create_task(...)["task"]["id"]` (the
  `.team.id` / `.task.id` wrap shape), cross-checked against team skill
  `homeric-crosshost-deployment-and-mesh-topology` (`jq -r '.team.id'  # NOT .id`).
- Added the JetStream nuance: JetStream already persists (`js_FileStorage`,
  `nats_client.cpp:90 cfg.Storage = js_FileStorage`) but to the EVENT STREAM, not
  the Store maps, and needs a live server CI does not have — reinforcing why
  in-process SQLite (server-less) is correct for deterministic unit tests.
- Added 5 new Failed Attempts rows for the still-unverified R1 items (unconfirmed
  Conan version `sqlite3/3.46.0`; assumed `SQLite::SQLite3` imported-target name
  from the Conan-generated config; unconfirmed exact NOLINT categories; nothing
  compiled/run) plus restated the JetStream-rejected-because-no-live-NATS-in-CI
  point. Updated the prior FetchContent-URL and Conan rows to reflect the reversal.
- Added `history:` frontmatter pointer; updated date 2026-06-20; bumped version to
  1.1.0; kept `verification: unverified`.
- Added tags: conan, find-package, clang-tidy, cppcheck, werror, nolint,
  imported-target, package-manager.

### Why

The R0 skill flagged its single most-uncertain external dependency (a
hand-written SQLite amalgamation URL guessed from memory) and several CI/build
assumptions as UNVERIFIED. The transferable methodology of the R1 pass is exactly
how to retire such flags WITHOUT building: de-risk the most-uncertain external
dependency by switching to the repo's already-proven dependency mechanism;
verify the CI gate's strictness against the actual cmake files before assuming new
code passes; verify a stated build constraint's premise against the real file; and
cite a confirmed source for any asserted API/JSON shape. Capturing this turns the
R0 "open questions" into a reusable de-risking procedure. It remains unverified
because no `conan install` / `just lint` / `ctest` was run this round.

